  "calendarNotes": "Fresno Unified begins the 2026–2027 school year on August 17, 2026 — earlier than most California districts, allowing the year to conclude before June's peak valley heat. Spring Break runs March 22–29, 2027. The school year ends June 10, 2027. Families relocating from districts that start after Labor Day should plan enrollment, childcare, and back-to-school shopping before mid-August.\n\nThe calendar includes California-specific no-school days — Lincoln's Birthday and Cesar Chavez Day — along with District Buyback Days when teachers attend professional development and students do not attend. The major multi-day breaks are Thanksgiving Break, Winter Break, and Spring Break; Fresno Unified does not have a Fall Break."
